who were hopeless, who inin the terms ofofofthe humanities, in the terms ofof theof the verities ofof man's condition,compassion and pity and courage, unselfishnesshe was inhuman, but he was stilla living man. He was not created to be a symbol of anything. He was simplycreated because suddenly he had a place inin that particular scene that I waswriting about, in that particular problem of human beings that I was writingabout. Not to symbolize anything at all.</template></category>
