<template>I think that man is trying to do what he does because he wants to, thathe himself does not always know why he wants to, but itit makes himfeel good. It makes his glands function right. People do foolhardy, reckless,dangerous things because it makes the glands flow good, makes them feel good. Ithink that man is not a gambler just to get a lot of money, that hegets some pleasure. His system works good when he is engaged in taking chancefor money or using his skill to gain money. The money is just a symbol of it. Ithink he would be a gambler if he werehad to gamble for matches. Iwould say that man does what he does because he wants to. No, sir, I don't. Only what I have learned about it fromlistening to people that do know.</template></category>
