<category><pattern>IN THE CREATION OF "THE BEAR," WERE YOU IN ANY WAY INFLUENCED BYMELVILLE</pattern>
<template>A writer, I have said several times this year and last year too, isinfluenced by everything he ever reads. Hehe himself doesn't bother.He knowshe doesn't think it important enough to say, "I wasinfluenced at this moment by so and so." He is omnivorous, voracious, andcompletely amoral. He is influenced by everything he ever reads. He will rob andsteal, right and left, with complete impunity, because he's not only perfectlywilling, but he's flattered when people after him rob and steal from him, thatif it's good enough for another writer to steal from him, it must have beenpretty good.So, if anything, he's flattered.I'm sure I was influenced by Melville, influenced by Flaubert, by the OldTestament, by everything that I ever read in the days when I read voraciouslywith no judgment.</template></category>
