<template>Well, she assumed when they got married that she was going to bechatelaine of a plantation, and they would have children. And she was going tobe asaccording to the rules of the booka good wife to him.She'd still be frigid and cold and a shrew probably, but she'd be a good wife.Then when he was going to throw the plantation away for idealistic folly, allshethe only revenge she had was that. At least he would have nochildren from her. He'd have no wife from her. And she hopedWell, Ike[excuse me, sir].</template></category>
