<category><pattern>WHAT AMERICAN WRITERSDO YOU ENJOY READING</pattern>
<template>I enjoy reading all of them, and I think all writers agree with me,except Faulkner, we'll say.Ithink that any writer must have an insatiable curiosity about people, andfiction books are simply the records of man in the moments of histriumphs or disasters, told by experts. For that reason, I doubt if any writerhas very much judgment about what he reads. He will read anything. As he getsolder, he will go back to certain books, to certain characters, as he would gointo another town, say, twenty five miles away to spend an afternoon with an oldfriend. That to the writer it doesn't matter who wrote that book, so I can'tspeak of books in terms of who wrote them, but there are books that I willalways like, that I loved when I was twenty-one years old, that I will still goback to.</template></category>
