<template>It begins with a seed. That seed could be anecdote. It could be asituation. It could be a character. Then you've got to explain how thatsituation came to be. You've got to explain where that character came from. Andthe first thing you know, you've got some more people in there explaining thesituation and the character. Then they all stand up andon their feetand begin to move, and all you've got to do is after that is to trot alongbehind them and put down what they do and say. That you canyou can invent the [finest,] mostwatertight plot you can think of. You get these people into it, and if they arehuman, unpredictable people, they won't care a hoot about that plot. They'll gooff and tell a story of their own. You can keep your plot. They don't wantit. did you find Absalom, Absalom!</template></category>
